---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import canaletto from '../assets/art/canaletto-grand-canal-rialto.jpg';
---

<section class="what" id="what">
  <div class="shell what__grid">
    <figure class="what__plate" data-reveal>
      <div class="frame">
        <Image
          src={canaletto}
          alt="A detail of Canaletto's Grand Canal: palace facades and gondolas mirrored in still water."
          widths={[480, 760, 1100]}
          sizes="(max-width: 880px) 90vw, 44vw"
          class="frame__img"
        />
      </div>
      <figcaption class="what__plate-cap label">
        Your wallpaper, a moment ago. Now it lives in <span class="mono">~/Pictures</span>.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="what__copy" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 90ms">
      <h2 class="section-title what__title">
        It lives in the menu bar and keeps the collection in your Pictures folder.
      </h2>
      <p class="what__body label measure">
        Veduta builds a library at <span class="mono">~/Pictures/VedutaLibrary</span>: a
        catalog, the collections you choose, and the paintings themselves. When a piece
        isn&rsquo;t on your Mac yet, it streams once from a public mirror, caches it, and from
        then on it is yours, offline.
      </p>
      <ul class="what__list">
        <li>
          <span class="what__k">No account, no cloud</span>
          <span class="what__v label">Nothing to sign in to. Nothing leaves your machine.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="what__k">Yours on disk</span>
          <span class="what__v label">Real image files you can open, copy, or back up like any other.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="what__k">Quiet by design</span>
          <span class="what__v label">A single menu-bar icon. No dock clutter, no notifications, no telemetry.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what {
    padding-top: var(--space-section);
  }

  .what__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.92fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 1rem + 5vw, 5rem);
  }

  .what__plate {
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* gilt frame, never a flat band */
  .frame {
    position: relative;
    padding: clamp(8px, 1vw, 14px);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: var(--frame-grad);
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 0 var(--brass-bright) inset,
      0 30px 60px -28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9),
      0 10px 24px -16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }
  .frame::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: clamp(8px, 1vw, 14px);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .frame__img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  .what__plate-cap {
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-mute);
  }

  .what__title {
    max-width: 18ch;
  }

  .what__body {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .what__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 2.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.1rem;
  }
  .what__list li {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    padding-top: 1.1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .what__k {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
  }
  .what__v {
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .mono {
    color: var(--brass);
  }

  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .what__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .what__plate {
      max-width: 32rem;
    }
  }
</style>
